---
import EditorialLayout from "../layouts/EditorialLayout.astro";
---

<EditorialLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Assembling Me"
  description="Privacy information for Assembling Me."
>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-8 py-24" id="main-content">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>
        Assembling Me is a personal site published by Joshua Tenner. The site does not currently
        offer accounts, comments, or a custom analytics product.
      </p>
      <h2>What this site collects</h2>
      <p>
        If you visit the site, your browser will make normal web requests to the hosting provider.
        Those requests may be logged by infrastructure such as GitHub Pages, CDNs, or your network
        provider.
      </p>
      <h2>Third-party requests</h2>
      <p>
        The site currently loads Google Fonts, and some noindex design-demo pages load externally
        hosted images. Those services may receive your IP address and standard browser request data
        when those assets are requested.
      </p>
      <h2>Email links</h2>
      <p>
        If you choose to email Joshua using a <code>mailto:</code> link, your message is handled by
        your email provider and Joshua&apos;s email provider.
      </p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy can be sent to <a href="mailto:tenner.joshua@gmail.com">tenner.joshua@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</EditorialLayout>
